#Approach:

Subarray Sum Equals K – Prefix Sum + HashMap Approach

Is problem me hume total count nikalna hota hai un subarrays ka jinka sum k ke equal ho.

Hum prefix sum use karte hain.
Har index par current prefix sum nikalte hain.
Agar kisi previous prefix sum ka value (currentPrefixSum - k) ho,
to iska matlab us previous index ke next se current index tak ka subarray sum k hoga.

Isliye HashMap me prefix sum ki frequency store karte hain.

Har step par:
current prefix sum nikalo
required value = prefixSum - k
agar ye value map me present hai, to uski frequency count me add kar do
phir current prefix sum ko map me update kar do

Important:
Map me starting me 0 ko frequency 1 ke saath store karte hain
taki wo subarrays bhi count ho saken jo index 0 se start hote hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:
class Solution {
    public int subarraySum(int[] nums, int k) {
        int cnt = 0;
        int presum = 0;
        int n = nums.length;
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        map.put(0,1);

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            presum += nums[i];
            int remove = presum - k;
            cnt += map.getOrDefault(remove, 0);

            map.put(presum, map.getOrDefault(presum, 0)+1);
        }
        return cnt;
    }
}
